NPM = Node Package Manager

Environment steup:
__________________
Two steps to setup angular
1. install NPM
2. setup angular application

What is the use of NPM in general?
NPM --> installs libraries + packages + applications

How to use NPM for angular setup?
NPM installs angular libraries
NPM executes scripts to transpiles our code & LAUNCH angular application

where to go?
www.npmjs.com

This package has installed:
	•	Node.js v8.9.4 to /usr/local/bin/node
	•	npm v5.6.0 to /usr/local/bin/npm
Make sure that /usr/local/bin is in your $PATH.

Steps for setting up angular application
_______________________________
OPTION A 
_______________________________
1. create application folder
2. add package def + configuration file
3. install packages
4. create the App's angular module
5. create main.ts 
6. create the HOST web page
_______________________________
OPTION B 
_______________________________
Angular CLI


Meaning - Angular is modular?
It has modules.
@angular/ core
@angular/ http
@angular/ router
@angular/ logging
@angular/ forms
@angular/ compiler
@angular/ typescript
@angular/ animations

Where can I see angular modules?
https://www.npmjs.com/~angular


What is angular DECORATOR?
It is similar to ANNOTATIONS in java. Looks like below:
@Component({
	selector: 'pm-root'
	templte: '<div><h1>{{ pageTitle}}</h1></div>'
})

How to import a Component?
import {Component} from '@angular/core';

SPA
- index.html is the main page of the application
- this is the ONLY web page of the application
- hence we call angular as SPA



